  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, two things that stand out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, somewhat dilapidated, to say the least, unshaven and otherwise.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I managed to go up to my parents' flat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father opened the door, and he was quite beside himself to see me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Remember that three weeks before my actual departure, he wouldn't even speak to me, he was so upset by this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was crying, and he was highly delighted to see me back safely and soundly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother was, of course, equally pleased to see me back, naturally.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And for the first time, I had a chance to have a proper wash and have a decent meal, and it was a question of getting back into the normal sort of daily routine.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I then ultimately went back to work again where I'd have to-- you had to use some sort of an excuse.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think I-- I mentioned that my father, who lived in Birmingham, was taken ill, and I had to look after him, some kind of a sob story.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I'd been away there without telling them what I was going to do, that I was going to be away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I didn't even know for how long.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was a little unpleasant and somewhat difficult, but you know, one overcomes these things.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The worst thing they could have done was to kick me out, and in those days, it wouldn't have been too difficult to find another job.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I then started training the people drawn from our movement, from Habonim, and we used the facilities that existed then and I think still exist today at the headquarters of Maccabi in London at Compayne Gardens.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
